1Ô∏è‚É£ Lab Purpose

This lab reinforces:

Linux directory management

File creation

Copying and moving files/folders

Deleting files and directories

Validating structure using CLI tools

Connecting to EC2 via SSH

It simulates a real-world company folder reorganization scenario.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Core Linux Commands Used
üìç Navigation Commands
pwd

Prints current working directory.

pwd

Example Output:

/home/ec2-user/CompanyA
cd

Changes directory.

cd foldername
cd ..
cd /home/ec2-user

Key concepts:

.. = parent directory

Absolute path starts with /

Relative path starts from current directory

ls

Lists files and folders.

ls
ls -la
ls -laR

Flags:

-l = long listing format

-a = show hidden files

-R = recursive (shows all subdirectories)

3Ô∏è‚É£ Directory Creation
mkdir

Creates new directory.

mkdir CompanyA
mkdir Finance HR Management

You can create multiple directories at once.

4Ô∏è‚É£ File Creation
touch

Creates empty files.

touch Salary.csv
touch file1.csv file2.csv

Important:

Does NOT add content

Creates empty placeholder files

5Ô∏è‚É£ Copying Files and Directories
cp
Copy file
cp file.txt destination/
Copy directory
cp -r Finance HR

‚ö†Ô∏è Important:

-r means recursive

Required when copying directories

Without -r, Linux will throw an error.

6Ô∏è‚É£ Moving Files and Directories
mv

Used to:

Move files

Move directories

Rename files

Example:

mv Management HR
mv file.txt Employees/

Key concept:
mv removes from original location automatically.

7Ô∏è‚É£ Deleting Files and Directories
rm

Deletes files.

rm file.csv

Delete multiple:

rm file1.csv file2.csv
rmdir

Removes empty directories ONLY.

rmdir Finance

If directory has files inside:

You will see:

Directory not empty
rm -r

Deletes directory and all contents recursively.

rm -r Finance

‚ö†Ô∏è Powerful command ‚Äî use carefully.

8Ô∏è‚É£ File System Structure Concepts
Absolute Path

Starts from root:

/home/ec2-user/CompanyA/Finance
Relative Path

Based on current location:

cd ../Finance
9Ô∏è‚É£ Recursive Validation

To verify entire structure:

ls -laR

This:

Displays permissions

Shows ownership

Shows file sizes

Shows nested directory structure

üîü SSH Connection Concepts

To connect to EC2:

ssh -i key.pem ec2-user@public-ip

Breakdown:

ssh = secure shell

-i = identity file

ec2-user = default Amazon Linux user

public-ip = EC2 instance address

Permission adjustment:

chmod 400 key.pem

This makes the key file read-only.

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Real-World Scenario

The lab simulates:

CompanyA restructuring departments:

Original:

CompanyA/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Finance
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ HR
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Management

New structure:

CompanyA/
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ HR/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Finance
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Management
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Employees

This represents:

Organizational restructuring

Department merging

File migration

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ Common Errors & Lessons Learned

‚ùå Trying to use rmdir on non-empty folder
‚úî Solution: Remove files first OR use rm -r

‚ùå Forgetting -r when copying directory
‚úî Solution: Always use cp -r for folders

‚ùå Wrong path usage
‚úî Use pwd frequently

‚ùå Not verifying changes
‚úî Use ls after every step

